cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with pose estimation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a novel architecture for learning image features and spatial models using convolutional networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the learning procedure and addresses the issue of vanishing gradients, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a sequential architecture for structured prediction tasks, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of belief maps and the demonstration of state-of-the-art performance on standard benchmarks suggest that the paper could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
